erroneous /ɪˈrəʊnɪəs/

1. ADJ Beliefs, opinions, or methods that are erroneous are incorrect or only partly correct. 错误的 

例： Some people have the erroneous notion that one can contract AIDS by giving blood. 有些人有这样一种错误的观念：认为献血会染上艾滋病。 

2. erroneously ADV 错误地 [ADV with v] 

例： It had been widely and erroneously reported that Armstrong had refused to give evidence. 曾经错误地大规模报道过阿姆斯特朗拒绝提供证据。

</div>

